                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00 Revolutions/4: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-19T10:00:00-06:00"
                            >April 19, 1931—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:26 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>61. Following telegram has been received from the American Vice Consul at
                    Tela.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“April 19, 3 a.m. Revolutionary forces moving towards Tela after capture
                        Progreso. New [<hi rend="italic">Now?</hi>] Tela being put under civilian
                        patrol. Request immediate despatch of marines by air”.</p>
                </quote>
                <p>Manager of the United Fruit Company reports that General Ramon Diaz advises that
                    he is leaving Progreso for Tela with 800 men and is operating in the name of
                    Ferrera. Company has ship in the harbor which it is holding to evacuate
                    Americans in case it is necessary. Revolution apparently spreading to all ports
                    on north coast and I therefore urge that one warship be sent at once to Tela and
                    one to Truxillo as well as the <hi rend="italic">Memphis</hi> to Ceiba.</p>
                <p>Forces also now moving on Truxillo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lay</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
